d3scan                                macro                               d3scan

NAME
     dd33ssccaann - three-motor scan relative to the starting positions

SYNOPSIS

     dd33ssccaann mm11 ssttaarrtt11 eenndd11 mm22 ssttaarrtt22 eenndd22 mm33 ssttaarrtt33 eenndd33 iinntteerrvvaallss ttiimmee

DESCRIPTION

     dd33ssccaann scans three motors, as specified by mmoottoorr11, mmoottoorr22 and mmoottoorr33. Each
     motor moves the same number of intervals.  If each motor is at a position XX
     before the scan begins, it will be scanned from XX++ssttaarrtt to XX++eenndd.  The step
     size for each motor is ((ssttaarrtt--eenndd))//iinntteerrvvaallss.  The number of data points
     collected will be iinntteerrvvaallss++11.  Count time is given by ttiimmee, which if
     positive, specifies seconds and if negative, specifies monitor counts.

     Upon termination, the motors are returned to their starting positions.

EXAMPLE

     dd33ssccaann tthh --11 11 pphhii --22 22 cchhii --11 11 2200 1100

